And when he's done, I'm gonna look through
the cards, and I'm gonna try

14:49.633 --> 14:51.667
to memorize the order very quickly.

14:51.733 --> 14:53.800
And then, after I've got the
order memorized,

14:53.867 --> 14:57.467
I'm gonna try to separate them out
into two piles, one with red cards,

14:57.533 --> 14:58.867
one with black cards.

14:58.933 --> 15:00.333
Let's see if I can do it.

15:14.567 --> 15:18.300
So if I did that right, we should have
all the red cards on one side,

15:18.600 --> 15:20.500
and all the black cards on the other side.
Let's see.

15:23.500 --> 15:25.500
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

15:27.000 --> 15:29.067
No, no, wait, wait, no, no.

15:29.133 --> 15:30.833
See, I, no, that's kind.

15:30.900 --> 15:33.333
It's kind, but I cannot accept
that much applause

15:33.400 --> 15:35.267
for a subpar memory demonstration.

15:35.367 --> 15:36.900
