15:38.800 --> 15:41.367
If I'm gonna fool them, I can't just do
something that's hard.

15:41.467 --> 15:43.500
I have got to do something
that is impossible.

15:43.767 --> 15:46.233
So, I'm gonna do the same thing again,

15:46.300 --> 15:48.500
but this time I'm gonna do it
with more cards.

15:48.800 --> 15:51.233
And I'm gonna memorize
the cards as I recite the poem,

15:51.300 --> 15:53.833
and then I'm gonna do
something impossible,

15:54.167 --> 15:55.600
which looks like this.

15:55.933 --> 15:57.700
Where was I?
"Mighty Casey at the bat."

15:57.767 --> 15:59.633
At the bat, that's right.
"10,000 eyes were on him

15:59.700 --> 16:01.767
"as he rubbed his hands with dirt.
5,000 tongues applauded

16:01.833 --> 16:02.967
"as he wiped them on his shirt.

16:03.033 --> 16:04.433
"Then while the writhing pitcher
ground the ball...

16:04.500 --> 16:07.833
"Defiance gleamed in Casey's eye,
a sneer curled Casey's lip.

16:10.200 --> 16:12.800
"And now the leather-covered
sphere comes hurling through the air,

16:12.867 --> 16:15.800
"and Casey stood a-watching
a haughty grandeur there.

16:16.067 --> 16:17.833
"Close by the sturdy batsman
the ball unheeded sped,

16:17.900 --> 16:20.133
"'That ain't my style,' said Casey.
'Strike one,' the umpire said.

16:20.200 --> 16:22.100
"He bade the game go on.
He signaled to the pitcher,

16:22.167 --> 16:23.867
"and again the dun sphere flew.

16:24.167 --> 16:27.400
"And Casey stood a-watching,
and the umpire said...

16:28.333 --> 16:29.867
"'Strike two!'"

16:30.333 --> 16:31.800
That's right.

16:31.933 --> 16:35.033
So, so I got these cards memorized.

16:35.100 --> 16:37.433
You can see there's about 19 of them,
maybe 21.

16:37.500 --> 16:38.933
There's 21.
I'm counting.

16:39.000 --> 16:43.900
And, Teller, with your help
I'm gonna change the order of these cards,

16:44.133 --> 16:48.100
so I can split them up into three piles,
four piles, five piles.

16:48.167 --> 16:50.367
How many piles should I split
the cards up into?

16:50.600 --> 16:51.767
Five piles.

16:51.833 --> 16:54.033
All right, then I'll try to take
out about a fifth of the cards

16:54.100 --> 16:56.400
here, that's pile number one.

16:56.633 --> 16:58.933
Two, three,

17:00.200 --> 17:02.800
four, and I got five, and another,
four and five.

17:03.267 --> 17:05.967
So now I just have to keep track
of which pile is which,

17:06.032 --> 17:08.267
which would have been easier
if you had picked three piles.

17:08.333 --> 17:09.666
Five makes it harder.

17:10.099 --> 17:12.933
Now I'm gonna reassemble them
in whichever order you want.

17:13.067 --> 17:15.099
So if you point to a pile,
