17:16.300 --> 17:17.400
Okay.

17:17.467 --> 17:18.567
Next.

17:28.733 --> 17:30.067
(LAUGHTER)

17:32.933 --> 17:35.133
And now, Penn, a number.

17:35.867 --> 17:36.933
Ten.

17:37.000 --> 17:38.067
Ten.

17:38.233 --> 17:41.500
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine, ten.

17:42.100 --> 17:44.067
Cut those to the bottom.
Teller, a number.

17:45.367 --> 17:46.433
Ten.

17:47.000 --> 17:50.133
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine, ten.

17:51.067 --> 17:52.633
So things are pretty simple
from this point on.

17:52.700 --> 17:55.500
All I gotta do is remember
the order the cards were in.

17:56.067 --> 17:58.533
Remember how we changed the
order, track every single one

17:58.600 --> 18:01.200
of the cards, and then split them
up into red and black piles

18:01.267 --> 18:03.067
as we conclude the poem.

18:03.900 --> 18:06.300
-Strike two.
-Strike two.

18:06.800 --> 18:08.300
I'll continue from there.

18:09.000 --> 18:13.700
"'Fraud!' cried the maddened thousands,
and the echo answered fraud.

18:14.033 --> 18:17.467
"But one scornful look from Casey
and the audience was awed.

18:17.767 --> 18:20.033
"They saw his face grow cold and stern,

18:20.100 --> 18:22.767
"they saw his muscles strain,
and they knew that Casey would

18:22.833 --> 18:23.967
"not let the ball go by again.

18:24.033 --> 18:25.067
"The smile has left from Casey's lips,

18:25.133 --> 18:26.200
"his teeth are clenched in hate.

18:26.267 --> 18:28.400
"He pounds with cruel violence
his bat upon the plate.

18:28.467 --> 18:30.333
"And now the pitcher holds the
ball, and now he lets it go,

18:30.400 --> 18:33.200
"and now the air is shattered
by the force of Casey's blow."

18:34.800 --> 18:36.000
(SIGHS)

18:37.567 --> 18:41.000
"Oh, somewhere in this favored
land the stars are shining bright.

18:42.167 --> 18:45.733
"The band is playing somewhere,
and somewhere hearts are light,

18:46.533 --> 18:50.467
"and somewhere men are laughing,
