18:50.833 --> 18:53.233
"but there is no joy in Mudville.

18:53.500 --> 18:54.900
"Mighty Casey has struck out."

18:55.200 --> 18:57.000
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

18:59.400 --> 19:01.200
Rick Lax, ladies and gentlemen.

19:01.267 --> 19:02.333
Wow.

19:03.733 --> 19:05.667
Well, you know how this works.
They're gonna sit down there.

19:05.733 --> 19:07.533
They're gonna deliberate.
Let me ask you about

19:07.600 --> 19:09.233
being here onstage because I think

19:09.300 --> 19:11.367
everyone who comes out here is courageous,

19:11.433 --> 19:13.433
but you've normally been behind
the scenes.

19:13.500 --> 19:16.733
That's right. Usually I create tricks for
other magicians,

19:16.800 --> 19:18.867
so this is a very new experience for me

19:18.933 --> 19:20.233
coming out here and performing
for everybody.

19:20.467 --> 19:22.100
I think it shows an enormous
amount of courage.

19:22.167 --> 19:26.800
Let's hear it for Rick, because to come
out here and do this here in this setting,

19:27.033 --> 19:29.767
wow, that takes a certain bravery.

19:30.067 --> 19:32.167
And maybe a certain foolishness
as well, I don't know.

19:32.233 --> 19:33.700
I don't know. But Teller looks...

19:34.000 --> 19:35.733
It's always hard to tell
what Teller looks like,

19:35.833 --> 19:37.633
but he looks a little surprised.

19:37.700 --> 19:38.867
-He looks a little bit...
RICK: I don't know.

19:38.933 --> 19:41.500
Okay, well, let's go over to him.
Penn, Teller.

19:42.333 --> 19:43.800
Boy, oh, boy.

19:44.367 --> 19:46.700
-That was a good routine.
RICK: Thank you.

19:46.767 --> 19:51.600
And not only that, it was a very, very
flattering routine to, you know,

19:51.667 --> 19:54.533
take <i>Casey at the Bat,</i> which we did
off Broadway and on Broadway.

19:54.700 --> 19:58.700
We're just very flattered by you
using all this Penn and Teller minutiae,

19:58.800 --> 20:00.967
all this trivia to make that so good.

20:01.033 --> 20:05.467
Your performance, I love,
I love the nervous, nutty energy.

20:05.900 --> 20:08.133
You got a little nervous.
Of course, when you sell this,

20:08.767 --> 20:10.867
gives us a lot of information about it,

20:11.467 --> 20:15.100
and we also copped a couple cards
from the table.

20:15.733 --> 20:21.533
We also saw you take the box
and put that box in your pocket.

20:21.667 --> 20:24.533
You put the box away
while you had the cards in your hand,

20:24.833 --> 20:27.000
which means you could have at that moment,

20:27.067 --> 20:31.433
have rung in a cooler,
and the cards could,

20:31.600 --> 20:37.300
in some way, be doctored for you to be
able to figure out which to go which way.

20:38.033 --> 20:41.767
All of that would be true if you
had not fooled us...

20:41.967 --> 20:43.367
(AUDIENCE GASPING)

20:43.433 --> 20:44.700
But you did.

20:44.833 --> 20:45.900
Wow.

20:45.967 --> 20:47.833
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

20:48.667 --> 20:50.367
Really? What a moment!

20:50.433 --> 20:51.600
Congratulations.

20:51.667 --> 20:53.567
The guys want to say,
go around the front there

20:53.633 --> 20:56.167
'cause they want to share with
you there while we bring this down.

20:56.700 --> 20:57.900
Here you go.

20:59.467 --> 21:01.467
We just don't know enough, man. Beautiful.

21:01.533 --> 21:02.767
Thank you.

21:02.967 --> 21:04.833
Rick, this is for you.

21:04.900 --> 21:06.067
-Thank you.
-You fooled them.

21:06.133 --> 21:08.033
You don't just get that delightful trophy,

21:08.733 --> 21:11.433
you'll be coming back here to perform
as part of their act.

21:12.433 --> 21:14.467
Rick Lax, congratulations.

21:15.800 --> 21:18.400
Now one act has already stumped
Penn and Teller and earned

21:18.467 --> 21:21.000
the priceless opportunity
to perform alongside them

21:21.067 --> 21:22.800
in their amazing Vegas show.

21:22.867 --> 21:23.933
Do I hear two?

21:24.000 --> 21:25.533
Let's meet our next potential fooler.

