My name is Marcus Eddie,
and I'm a creator.

21:33.567 --> 21:35.333
I think one of the biggest
advantages I have in this show

21:35.400 --> 21:38.300
is that I do create my own magic,
and so what you're going

21:38.367 --> 21:40.100
<i>to see is something original.</i>

21:40.300 --> 21:42.600
<i>My favorite type of magic</i>
<i>is impromptu magic.</i>

21:42.767 --> 21:45.200
<i>I can walk into any place and</i>
<i>pick up something</i>

21:45.300 --> 21:47.033
<i>and immediately do magic with it.</i>

21:50.233 --> 21:53.233
<i>My daughter Alysa helps me out</i>
<i>with some of the magic ideas that I have.</i>

21:53.300 --> 21:54.733
That was great.

21:54.800 --> 21:55.933
Can you do it again?
Do it again.

21:56.067 --> 21:57.933
Of course, children have that
great imagination,

21:58.000 --> 22:01.867
and I just love having a jam session
with her about magical ideas.

22:02.133 --> 22:03.567
<i>That totally gets my mind working.</i>

22:03.700 --> 22:06.333
I truly believe that I can
change my life

22:06.400 --> 22:08.800
and the life of my family,
doing what I do.

22:09.800 --> 22:11.133
(APPLAUSE)

22:11.333 --> 22:13.333
Will you please welcome Marcus Eddie.

22:13.433 --> 22:15.533
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

22:20.400 --> 22:23.633
My name is Marcus Eddie,
and magic has always been...

22:24.133 --> 22:25.467
My escape.

22:25.633 --> 22:27.067
That's why...

22:28.000 --> 22:30.233
I've had this key with me
ever since I was a kid

22:30.533 --> 22:32.333
to remind myself that

22:32.567 --> 22:35.000
I can always unlock my
imagination to get through...

22:36.233 --> 22:37.300
Anything.

22:37.367 --> 22:38.700
(APPLAUSE)

22:43.133 --> 22:46.967
Now I first realized this when studying
one of my favorite magicians,

22:47.167 --> 22:49.967
Harry Houdini, who was also

22:50.567 --> 22:53.433
one of the greatest escape artists
of all time.

22:56.167 --> 22:58.967
Harry Houdini would defy
the laws of physics by passing

22:59.033 --> 23:04.600
his body through solid brick walls,
which to some is the only way

23:04.867 --> 23:07.233
he was able to escape from
handcuffs...

23:09.133 --> 23:10.333
And chains.

23:11.033 --> 23:15.433
Harry Houdini will be a symbol,
a voice for generations to come,

23:15.633 --> 23:18.333
challenging fear every time
he stepped on that stage

23:18.633 --> 23:20.867
saying, "Nothing can hold me."

23:22.967 --> 23:24.300
(APPLAUSE)

23:30.333 --> 23:34.367
Now, the idea of passing through
solid objects is what inspired me

23:34.433 --> 23:37.367
to create something very
special for you, Penn and Teller.

23:37.633 --> 23:39.233
Would you both mind joining me on stage?

23:39.300 --> 23:41.267
Everyone, please help me welcome
Penn and Teller.

23:41.333 --> 23:43.600
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

23:44.433 --> 23:45.933
Hello, Marcus. How you doing?

